17
00:01:33,140 --> 00:01:36,110
{\an2}{\pos(212,244.95)}第三季  第八集

18
00:01:44,580 --> 00:01:48,150
当大西洋的表层水温高于80度时
When surface temperatures in the Atlantic rise above 80 degrees,

19
00:01:48,150 --> 00:01:50,350
是飓风形成的理想条件
conditions are ideal for a hurricane.

20
00:01:50,970 --> 00:01:53,560
西风激起冷凝作用
Westerly winds kick up condensation,

21
00:01:53,740 --> 00:01:58,450
生成绕中央轴旋转的积雨云
forming cumulonimbus clouds which begin to revolve around a central axis.

22
00:01:58,690 --> 00:02:03,410
9月7日  以上条件生成了飓风费斯
On September seventh, these exact conditions gave birth to the Hurricane Faith.

23
00:02:03,410 --> 00:02:07,280
现在正向美国东海岸推进
currently barreling toward the Eastern seaboard of the United States.

24
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:10,980
1984年11月7日
On November 7th, 1984,

25
00:02:11,070 --> 00:02:13,990
生成了另一种类型的飓风
a different sort of hurricane swirled into being.

26
00:02:14,370 --> 00:02:17,060
一个25岁的哈佛法学院毕业生
A 25-year-old Harvard Law graduate

27
00:02:17,060 --> 00:02:20,890
席卷了南卡罗莱纳州州参议院第14区
took South Carolina State Senate District Fourteen by storm.

28
00:02:21,600 --> 00:02:24,940
他的名字是弗兰西斯·J·安德伍德
His name was Francis J. Underwood.

29
00:02:24,990 --> 00:02:26,730
飓风登陆的话有多强
How strong will it be when it hits?

30
00:02:26,730 --> 00:02:29,700
模拟软件显示有三级  甚至四级
Simulators say Cat Three, possibly Cat Four.

31
00:02:30,060 --> 00:02:32,290
将给数十个州造成极大破坏
Major devastation across a dozen states.

32
00:02:32,660 --> 00:02:35,390
但有些模拟路线显示可能会转向大海
Yes, but some of these projections have it turning back to sea.

33
00:02:35,790 --> 00:02:37,370
不太可能  先生
That's highly unlikely, sir.

34
00:02:38,330 --> 00:02:40,900
先生  联邦应急管理署就是要为最坏情况做打算
Sir, FEMA's mission is to prepare for the worst.

35
00:02:40,900 --> 00:02:44,180
现场急救员  医疗  大面积撤离
First responders, medical, mass evacuation.

36
00:02:44,620 --> 00:02:46,130
我很担心资金问题
I'm worried about the funding.

37
00:02:47,350 --> 00:02:50,200
《美就法》启动后  联邦应急管理署赈灾资金
The Disaster Relief Fund has been depleted by a third

38
00:02:50,200 --> 00:02:51,310
耗掉了三分之一
since you launched AmWorks.

39
00:02:51,310 --> 00:02:52,700
那还有二十亿
That still leaves two billion.

40
00:02:52,700 --> 00:02:55,510
应对这种级别的飓风  我们需要四倍的资金
Well, for this storm, we need four times that.

41
00:02:56,580 --> 00:02:58,010
我这就要去见领导层
I'm about to meet with the leadership

42
00:02:58,010 --> 00:02:59,320
请他们补充资金
to ask them to replenish the fund,

43
00:02:59,320 --> 00:03:00,520
但我不能要那么多钱
but I can't ask for that much.

44
00:03:00,530 --> 00:03:03,890
我们需要最少八十亿的基础准备资金
We need eight billion minimum for bare-bones preparation.

45
00:03:04,820 --> 00:03:06,930
我们还是不要冒这种险  先生
We shouldn't gamble with something like this, sir.

46
00:03:07,240 --> 00:03:09,280
成百上千的人可能会丧命
Hundreds could die. Maybe thousands.

47
00:03:10,890 --> 00:03:12,900
"不可能成了可能
"The impossible made possible.

48
00:03:13,270 --> 00:03:15,590
无人敢做的事
The thing no one else dares to do,

49
00:03:15,590 --> 00:03:18,010
所有人都说办不到的事
that everyone says can't be done.

50
00:03:18,600 --> 00:03:22,200
设想一下  一个男孩站在查尔斯顿港海边
Imagine a boy standing on the shores of the Charleston Harbor.

51
00:03:23,110 --> 00:03:27,720
两英里开外  隐约能看到萨姆特堡
Two miles away, a faint line on the horizon, is Fort Sumter.

52
00:03:28,460 --> 00:03:31,440
其他男孩都说不可能游到那里去
All the other boys say it's impossible to swim there.

53
00:03:32,610 --> 00:03:35,730
但这个男孩  却觉得能做到
But this one boy thinks it can be done.

54
00:03:36,040 --> 00:03:38,550
周围人都倒吸一口冷气  看着他脱下鞋
The others gasp as he kicks off his shoes,

55
00:03:38,550 --> 00:03:39,860
跳入海里
plunges into the water.

56
00:03:40,230 --> 00:03:43,070
他们吃惊地看着他越游越远
They watch with shock as he grows farther from the shore.

57
00:03:44,890 --> 00:03:46,890
他们紧张地交头接耳
They whisper to each other solemnly,

58
00:03:46,920 --> 00:03:48,910
'他会淹死  他办不到的'
'He'll drown. He'll never make it.'

59
00:03:49,250 --> 00:03:51,450
'不  他游不下去时会掉头的'"
'No, he'll turn around when it gets too hard.'"

60
00:03:51,450 --> 00:03:52,300
总统先生
Mr. President.

61
00:03:53,130 --> 00:03:55,650
请坐  我叫杰西卡送点喝的来
Have a seat. I'll have Jessica bring in some refreshments.

62
00:03:56,080 --> 00:03:58,680
亨利·米切尔  新任参议院多数党领袖
Henry Mitchell, the new Senate Majority Leader.

63
00:03:58,790 --> 00:04:00,220
赫克特·门多萨怎么了
What happened to Hector Mendoza?

64
00:04:00,220 --> 00:04:03,060
你不把有偿演讲当作收入上报
Well, you don't declare a couple of paid speeches as income

65
00:04:03,060 --> 00:04:04,940
你转眼就被踢出国会了
and boom, you're no longer in Congress,

66
00:04:04,940 --> 00:04:06,640
当然也就不能参加总统选举了
and certainly not running for president.

67
00:04:06,900 --> 00:04:09,840
你把罗尼那幅画扔了  赫克特很喜欢那幅画
You got rid of Ronnie. Hector loved that painting.

68
00:04:09,840 --> 00:04:11,960
没扔  只是放起来了
He's not gone, just in storage.

69
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:13,100
赫克特也去积灰了
Just like Hector.

70
00:04:13,140 --> 00:04:15,100
我父亲在艾森豪威尔手下卖命
My father served under Eisenhower.

71
00:04:15,270 --> 00:04:16,560
在诺曼底给他开吉普车
Drove his jeep in Normandy.

72
00:04:16,960 --> 00:04:18,910
你父亲参加登陆日了吗
Your father was at D-Day?

73
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:21,870
犹他海滩  还有巴斯托涅
Utah Beach. At Bastogne too.

74
00:04:22,060 --> 00:04:24,140
真是爱意满满啊
Isn't this just a little love fest.

75
00:04:24,990 --> 00:04:28,680
先生们  飓风问题  我需要补充赈灾资金
Gentlemen, the hurricane. I need the DRF replenished.

76
00:04:29,520 --> 00:04:32,000
议长今晚将召开紧急会议
The Speaker's calling for an emergency session tonight.

77
00:04:32,020 --> 00:04:34,240
我们准备拨出一百亿资金
We're prepared to allocate ten billion.

78
00:04:34,640 --> 00:04:36,560
我本只想要八十亿
I was only gonna ask for eight.

79
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:39,360
签了法案  就有一百亿
You sign the bill, you'll get the ten billion.

80
00:04:39,820 --> 00:04:43,160
但联邦应急管理署或者其他机构的资金
But no FEMA money or any other agency funds can be used

81
00:04:43,170 --> 00:04:46,100
在任何情况下都不能再给你的就业法案了
for your jobs program again, under any circumstances.

82
00:04:46,100 --> 00:04:47,770
别把这事扯到政治上去
Don't politicize this.

83
00:04:47,770 --> 00:04:50,900
《美国就业法案》和飓风是两码事
America Works and the hurricane are two separate issues.

84
00:04:51,040 --> 00:04:53,050
不好意思  总统先生
Excuse me, Mr. President,

85
00:04:53,070 --> 00:04:55,970
是你把赈灾资金用于了政治用途
but you're the one that raided the DRF for political purposes.

86
00:04:55,990 --> 00:04:57,560
我们是在纠正错误
We're correcting a wrong.

87
00:04:57,560 --> 00:05:00,110
还危及到整个东海岸
And jeopardizing the entire Eastern Seaboard.

88
00:05:00,110 --> 00:05:02,210
这得怪白宫  与我们无关
That's on the White House, not on us.

89
00:05:02,210 --> 00:05:05,210
我们会补充资金  填补被你非法挪用的钱
We're supplying the funds, the money you took illegally.

90
00:05:05,210 --> 00:05:08,450
你要是不签这个法案  也怪不了我们
If you choose not to sign the bill, we can't be blamed.

91
00:05:08,450 --> 00:05:09,530
我们提过议了
We stepped up.

92
00:05:13,660 --> 00:05:16,380
我就猜你们会扯上《美国就业法案》
I thought you might try to make this about America Works.

93
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:19,410
我承认  我也许是过线了
And look, I admit, I may have overstepped.

94
00:05:19,410 --> 00:05:21,200
不过  我给你们看点东西
But let me show you something.

95
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:23,210
每天我都让新闻部
Every day, I ask the Comms office

96
00:05:23,220 --> 00:05:27,380
给我十份《美国就业法案》受益人的介绍
to give me profiles of ten AmWorks beneficiaries.

97
00:05:27,450 --> 00:05:28,890
这些是成功案例
These are success stories.

98
00:05:28,890 --> 00:05:30,320
这只是我们
This is just a fraction

99
00:05:30,320 --> 00:05:33,330
帮助重回岗位的四万人中的一小部分
of the 40,000 people that we put back to work.

100
00:05:33,330 --> 00:05:36,480
用本来不是做这个的钱
With money that wasn't appropriated for that purpose.

101
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:38,700
你不可以把扑满打破后
You don't get to break the piggy bank

102
00:05:38,700 --> 00:05:41,850
还让我们粘回去  再往里放更多的钱
then ask us to glue it together and put in more pennies.

103
00:05:41,850 --> 00:05:45,250
参众两院有超过五十名民主党及共和党议员
I've got over 50 Democrats and Republicans in both houses

104
00:05:45,250 --> 00:05:46,590
在法案提出后
that have publicly supported

105
00:05:46,590 --> 00:05:48,950
公开表示支持《美国就业法案》
America Works since its introduction.

106
00:05:48,960 --> 00:05:50,360
风头变了
The tide is turning.

107
00:05:50,360 --> 00:05:52,440
你们自己人都在支持法案
Your own people are getting behind the program.

108
00:05:52,440 --> 00:05:55,470
他们现在在哪  为什么没人打电话给我们
Then where are they now? Why aren't we getting calls?

109
00:05:56,160 --> 00:05:59,130
他们为什么都支持这一应急法案
Why do they all support this emergency bill?

110
00:05:59,130 --> 00:06:00,620
如果你们投票通过  我就会行使否决权
If you pass it, I'll veto it,

111
00:06:00,620 --> 00:06:03,590
可这样斗气毫无意义
but there's no reason we have to turn this into a pissing match.

112
00:06:03,590 --> 00:06:06,480
你知道我们有足够票数推翻你的否决
You know that we have the votes to override your veto.

113
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:09,320
就算你不签字  十天之后也会通过
It passes in ten days without a signature, regardless.

114
00:06:09,320 --> 00:06:10,760
唯一的区别
The only question

115
00:06:10,930 --> 00:06:14,120
是你会在飓风到来之前签字同意
is whether you're gonna sign it before that hurricane hits,

116
00:06:14,200 --> 00:06:17,990
还是在数千人死去之后看着法案通过
or watch it become law after thousands have died.

117
00:06:18,580 --> 00:06:19,410
亨利
Henry...

118
00:06:20,520 --> 00:06:22,750
我曾与赫克特
I sat with Hector

119
00:06:22,860 --> 00:06:25,680
数十次坐在这张桌子旁边
dozens of times at this very table

120
00:06:25,680 --> 00:06:27,260
通过谈判
and we were always able

121
00:06:27,260 --> 00:06:30,310
解决我们的争端
to work out our differences, to negotiate.

122
00:06:30,310 --> 00:06:32,340
这已经不再是赫克特的办公室
This isn't Hector's office anymore.

123
00:06:33,580 --> 00:06:34,640
或是他的桌子了
Or his table.

124
00:06:34,740 --> 00:06:38,060
先生们  没有回旋的余地了吗
Gentlemen, is there no room for a compromise?

125
00:06:38,270 --> 00:06:40,320
-没有  -鲍勃
- No. - Bob?

126
00:06:40,320 --> 00:06:41,680
没有了  总统先生
No, Mr. President.

127
00:06:43,870 --> 00:06:45,400
消息一小时后就会发布
It's going wide in an hour.

128
00:06:45,460 --> 00:06:47,880
七位州长  整个东海岸上下
Seven governors, all up and down the East Coast.

129
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:49,540
都要求您签字同意
They're demanding that you sign the bill.

130
00:06:49,540 --> 00:06:51,780
-谁告诉你的  -吉姆·马修斯的宣传员
- Who tipped you off? - Jim Matthews' flack.

131
00:06:51,780 --> 00:06:54,010
马修斯背叛我们了吗  怎么说的
Matthews is turning on us? What's it say?

132
00:06:54,430 --> 00:06:57,270
"安德伍德总统低估了分权制度
"President Underwood has undermined the separation of powers

133
00:06:57,270 --> 00:06:59,270
并将整个东海岸的命运
and put the fate of the entire East Coast

134
00:06:59,270 --> 00:07:00,820
交予飓风费斯之手
in Hurricane Faith's hands.

135
00:07:00,820 --> 00:07:02,020
我与以下各位州长
I am joining with the Governors

136
00:07:02,020 --> 00:07:04,220
北卡罗来纳  维吉尼亚  马里兰..."
of North Carolina, Virginia, Maryland--"

137
00:07:04,220 --> 00:07:05,920
够了  我不用再听了
That's enough. I don't need to hear any more.

138
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:08,740
看三十分钟内你能联系到多少位州长
See how many governors you can get on the phone in 30 minutes.

139
00:07:08,740 --> 00:07:10,970
-好的  -我还有东西给您
- Yes, sir. - I've got something else for you, sir.

140
00:07:10,970 --> 00:07:13,100
《美就法》个案  这是今天的十位
The AmWorks case studies. These are your ten for the day.

141
00:07:13,100 --> 00:07:16,280
-我现在没时间看  -您该看看第一份
- I don't have time for that now. - You should see this top file.

142
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:29,030
弗莱迪现在是一名洗碗工
Freddy's working as a dishwasher.

143
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,330
他是最早注册的人之一
He was one of the first people to sign up.

144
00:07:38,180 --> 00:07:40,550
我要写一份声明回应这些州长吗
Should I prepare a statement in response to the governors?

145
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:43,920
先生
Sir?

146
00:07:45,170 --> 00:07:46,930
不用写声明  暂时不用
No statement. No. Not yet.

147
00:07:47,340 --> 00:07:48,050
好的
Yes, sir.

148
00:07:52,940 --> 00:07:54,920
-先生  -给全体内阁发消息
- Yes, sir? - Send a message to the entire cabinet.

149
00:07:54,920 --> 00:07:56,630
明天一早就开个会
I want a meeting tomorrow morning, first thing.

150
00:07:59,090 --> 00:08:00,630
"众所周知
"During his tenure as whip,

151
00:08:00,630 --> 00:08:03,480
安德伍德担任党鞭期间常采取恐吓
Underwood was known for employing intimidation,

152
00:08:03,480 --> 00:08:05,180
虚张声势和威慑等手段
bravado and fear.

153
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,590
他最近对俄罗斯采取的立场
His recent stance against Russia

154
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:10,190
延续了他一贯的暴力外交手段
is a continuation of strong-arm diplomacy,

155
00:08:10,190 --> 00:08:13,770
他顶着参议院反对所任命的联合国大使
carried out by his wife, whom he appointed UN ambassador

156
00:08:13,770 --> 00:08:15,960
他妻子执行了他的策略
despite the Senate voting her down.

157
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:19,270
用联邦应急管理署资金资助《美国就业法案》
The use of FEMA funds for America Works

158
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:20,190
令很多人震惊
shocked many,

159
00:08:20,490 --> 00:08:21,930
但这只是他职业生涯中
but it's simply the most recent

160
00:08:21,930 --> 00:08:24,740
一贯独断专行作风的最新案例
in a career's worth of unilateral moves.

161
00:08:25,610 --> 00:08:27,660
少数党领袖鲍勃·博奇说 
Minority Leader Bob Birch said,

162
00:08:27,840 --> 00:08:30,820
总统的行为一直体现出
'The President consistently demonstrates an utter

163
00:08:30,820 --> 00:08:34,500
他的缺乏合作精神和恣意妄为"
lack of partnership coupled with reckless abandon.'"

164
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,840
先生  您考虑过
Sir, have you given any thought

165
00:08:36,860 --> 00:08:40,150
直接在国会昨晚通过的法案上签字吗
to simply signing the bill that Congress passed last night?

166
00:08:48,050 --> 00:08:50,310
有多少人认为我该签字的
How many of you think I should sign the bill?

167
00:08:51,460 --> 00:08:53,400
肯定有人认为我该签字
Well, surely, some of you think I should.

