00:13:10,840 --> 00:13:12,900
谈话要点  又准备学这一招吗
my talking points on the FEMA bill?

234
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:14,170
你点子好
You made good points.

235
00:13:14,790 --> 00:13:17,190
对手要是正确  我也愿意拥护
I'm not above agreeing with the opposition when they're right.

236
00:13:19,550 --> 00:13:21,720
但我没想到你立场这么鲜明
But I'm surprised you've been so critical.

237
00:13:21,750 --> 00:13:23,910
我以为你和安德伍德关系很好
I thought you and Underwood were close.

238
00:13:23,910 --> 00:13:26,680
盟友如果犯错  我也会表示反对
I'm not above disagreeing with an ally when they're wrong.

239
00:13:29,510 --> 00:13:30,500
既然要做正确的事
In the spirit of what's right,

240
