331
00:17:52,810 --> 00:17:55,950
不过  希望还是有的
But... there's still some hope.

332
00:17:57,260 --> 00:17:58,940
放松一下吧  弗兰西斯
Relax for a minute, Francis.

333
00:18:03,970 --> 00:18:06,230
应该取消明天的联合国维和部队出征仪式
We should cancel the UN ceremony tomorrow.

334
00:18:06,230 --> 00:18:08,480
-什么  -也许这有些不合时宜
- What? - Maybe it sends the wrong message.

335
00:18:08,480 --> 00:18:11,980
不  这是你的大胜利  是我们的胜利
No, it's a great victory for you. For us.

336
00:18:12,070 --> 00:18:13,950
但是大灾当前却还开庆典...
But celebrating in the middle of a crisis, I don't--

337
00:18:13,950 --> 00:18:16,080
这种时候我们就该这么做
Well, that's exactly what we should be doing.

338
00:18:17,150 --> 00:18:19,160
你促成了这个决议案
You made this resolution happen.

339
00:18:19,260 --> 00:18:21,050
这是我们搬进白宫之后
It's the one good notch we have

340
00:18:21,050 --> 00:18:23,130
取得的仅有的一桩像样的成绩
on our belt since we moved into the White House.

341
00:18:23,130 --> 00:18:26,620
我绝不会让这飓风抢走我们庆祝的机会
I'll be damned if I'm gonna let this hurricane rob us of that.

342
00:18:30,460 --> 00:18:33,030
"当国会拒绝支持向约旦河谷
"When Congress refused to support a peacekeeping mission

343
00:18:33,040 --> 00:18:36,210
派驻维和部队后  总统还是派出了部队
in the Jordan Valley, the president deployed troops anyway,

344
00:18:36,650 --> 00:18:39,320
彰显他作为三军统帅的权威"
stating his authority as Commander in Chief."

345
00:18:40,060 --> 00:18:43,110
"距离城堡外墙还有一英里
"The ramparts of the fort were still a mile away.

346
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:45,690
但他已经游得太远  进退不得
But he had reached the point of no return.

347
00:18:45,920 --> 00:18:48,550
掉头回去已经不可能了"
Turning back was no longer an option."

348
00:18:49,690 --> 00:18:51,540
"全世界都在关注着他
"With the world's eyes upon him,

349
00:18:51,540 --> 00:18:53,810
他继续无视种种先例
he continues to ignore precedent,

350
00:18:54,020 --> 00:18:57,020
常规  甚至有人觉得他无视法律"
convention, and some would say the law."

351
00:18:57,940 --> 00:18:59,810
"他为什么要跨越那条隐形的返回线
"Why did he cross that invisible line?

352
00:19:00,700 --> 00:19:01,750
为什么甘冒生命危险
Why risk his life

353
00:19:01,750 --> 00:19:04,200
哪怕成功的几率是如此之低"
despite the great odds stacked against him?"

354
00:19:05,670 --> 00:19:08,740
"批评十分尖锐  但大部分的批评都
"Critics have been harsh. And yet most have stopped

355
00:19:08,740 --> 00:19:12,940
没有揭示安德伍德真实的面目  暴君"
short of naming Underwood what he truly is: a tyrant."

356
00:19:14,200 --> 00:19:17,400
"是什么驱使拿破仑坚持向莫斯科进军
"What drove Napoleon to keep marching toward Moscow?

357
00:19:17,580 --> 00:19:19,360
或者让汉尼拔越过阿尔卑斯山"
Or Hannibal to cross the Alps?"

358
00:19:19,790 --> 00:19:21,350
"警钟已然敲响
"The warning signs are there.

359
00:19:21,350 --> 00:19:23,740
我们有责任警觉起来"
It's our responsibility to heed them."

360
00:19:23,740 --> 00:19:25,960
"又是什么支撑着年轻的弗兰克·安德伍德
"What kept a young Frank Underwood

361
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:27,210
继续游下去
swimming onward?

362
00:19:27,350 --> 00:19:28,940
是什么使他没有淹死呢"
And what kept him from drowning?"

363
00:19:31,430 --> 00:19:33,040
赛斯怎么知道的
How did Seth learn this?

364
00:19:33,130 --> 00:19:35,930
-杰姬的新闻主管  -是昨晚的事吗
- Jackie's comms director. - And this happened last night?

365
00:19:35,930 --> 00:19:36,800
据我所知是这样
From what I can gather.

366
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,230
那怎么现在才告诉我
So why am I just hearing about it now?

367
00:19:38,230 --> 00:19:39,530
之前怎么没人提醒我
I didn't hear about it before it happens.

368
00:19:39,530 --> 00:19:41,090
她显然是不想让别人知道
Obviously, she was trying to keep it a secret.

369
00:19:41,090 --> 00:19:42,890
但你不是盯着她呢吗
But you're supposed to be keeping tabs on her.

370
00:19:42,890 --> 00:19:45,420
结果你不仅不知道  还得赛斯告诉你
The fact that you didn't know, and only found out from Seth--

371
00:19:45,420 --> 00:19:46,380
我不在爱荷华  先生
I'm not in Iowa, sir.

372
00:19:46,380 --> 00:19:47,660
我在华盛顿管理你的团队
I'm here running your staff.

373
00:19:47,660 --> 00:19:48,460
你说什么
Excuse me?

374
00:19:48,480 --> 00:19:50,110
尽管我和杰姬有一段过往
Just because Jackie and I have a personal history

375
00:19:50,110 --> 00:19:51,520
不代表我知道她的一举一动
doesn't mean I know her every movement.

376
00:19:52,330 --> 00:19:54,700
我们说的不是你的前女友
We are not talking about your ex-girlfriend.

377
00:19:54,700 --> 00:19:56,660
我们说的是我的竞选伙伴
We're talking about my running mate.

378
00:19:56,660 --> 00:19:58,070
如果我们不能信任她
And if she can't be trusted,

379
00:19:58,070 --> 00:20:00,160
那她不想说的话我也没法逼她说
I can't force her to reveal things she doesn't want to.

380
00:20:00,160 --> 00:20:01,390
当初就是你力主
You are the one who convinced me

381
00:20:01,390 --> 00:20:02,900
我和她做交易的
to make the deal with her in the first place.

382
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:04,850
我们需要信息  她有门路搞到信息
We needed information. She had access.

383
00:20:04,850 --> 00:20:06,220
结果现在她欺瞒我们
And now she's lying to us.

384
00:20:06,550 --> 00:20:08,970
也许认定此事为危机之前  你该先和她谈一谈
Maybe you should speak with her before we consider this a crisis.

385
00:20:09,010 --> 00:20:10,470
我不喜欢你的语气  雷米
I don't like your tone, Remy.

386
00:20:10,470 --> 00:20:13,220
-你反应过度了  -你给我注意点
- You're blowing this out of proportion. - Watch yourself.

387
00:20:13,330 --> 00:20:14,740
之前在国会  我为你工作时
When I worked for you in Congress,

388
00:20:14,740 --> 00:20:16,110
你一向让我对你有话直说
you always told me to be straight up with you.

389
00:20:16,120 --> 00:20:17,800
那时候我不是总统
I wasn't the president then.

390
00:20:18,140 --> 00:20:21,040
那你是想让我低头道歉做应声虫了
So you just want me to apologize and be a yes-man?

391
00:20:21,040 --> 00:20:23,820
我要你对总统放尊重些
I want you to treat this office with respect.

392
00:20:23,820 --> 00:20:25,530
那你也该对你的手下尊重点
You owe your staff that same respect.

393
00:20:25,530 --> 00:20:27,340
你当初走投无路的时候
I gave you a position in the White House

394
00:20:27,340 --> 00:20:28,610
我收容你在白宫供职
when no one would touch you.

395
00:20:28,620 --> 00:20:30,430
我什么都不欠你的
I don't owe you a damn thing.

396
00:20:30,430 --> 00:20:31,700
你打算拿这个说事说多久
How long you gonna hang that over my head?

397
00:20:31,700 --> 00:20:33,620
你简直像是想让我解雇你
Oh, it's like you want me to fire you.

398
00:20:33,620 --> 00:20:35,140
你不能解雇我  你心里明白
You couldn't, and you know it.

399
00:20:37,280 --> 00:20:38,280
至少现在不能
Not right now.

400
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:41,210
赛斯和我是你仅有的两个小兵
Seth and I are the only two soldiers you have.

401
00:20:43,830 --> 00:20:47,070
-接通杰姬的电话  -遵命  先生
- Get Jackie on the phone. - Yes, sir.

402
00:21:12,750 --> 00:21:14,630
先生  夏普议员的电话
Sir, Congresswoman Sharp calling for you.

403
00:21:14,920 --> 00:21:16,030
我就在这里接
I'll take it in here.

404
00:21:22,950 --> 00:21:24,970
先生  我们可以替您擦鞋的
Sir, we'll gladly polish those for you.

405
00:21:25,030 --> 00:21:26,850
我乐意自己来  谢谢
I'm happy to do it myself. Thank you.

406
00:21:27,950 --> 00:21:28,700
好的  先生
Yes, sir.

407
00:21:35,010 --> 00:21:35,950
议员女士
Congresswoman.

408
00:21:36,030 --> 00:21:37,650
抱歉您可能会听到咀嚼声
I apologize if you hear chewing.

409
00:21:37,780 --> 00:21:38,510
这是我今天
This is the first chance

410
00:21:38,510 --> 00:21:40,470
第一次有机会吃饭  日程太满了
I've gotten to eat all day. Non-stop events.

411
00:21:40,470 --> 00:21:43,470
我很惊讶你在见过邓巴之后居然还有胃口
I'm surprised you have an appetite after meeting with Dunbar.

412
00:21:47,670 --> 00:21:50,020
她的人要求见面  我同意了
Her people asked. I said yes.

413
00:21:50,020 --> 00:21:52,710
我想在打扰您之前先看看她想要什么
I thought I'd see what she wanted before bothering you with it.

414
00:21:52,710 --> 00:21:56,300
让你暂停竞选活动吗  你拒绝她了吧
Suspending your campaigns? I'm assuming that you told her no.

415
00:21:59,360 --> 00:22:00,410
我同意了
I told her yes.

416
00:22:02,070 --> 00:22:02,960
你明白她这是在
You realize she's just

417
00:22:02,960 --> 00:22:05,340
利用你的善良来阻碍你筹款吧
preying upon your good nature to stop your fundraising.

418
00:22:05,340 --> 00:22:08,580
即使是这样  这在政治上对我也有好处
Even if that were the case, the politics work in my favor too.

419
00:22:08,580 --> 00:22:11,460
在这么大的灾难面前继续竞选是不应该的
It's insensitive to campaign during a catastrophe this big.

420
00:22:11,470 --> 00:22:12,730
可能对我造成不良影响
It could backfire on me.

421
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:15,490
我们并不确定一定就会有大灾难发生
We don't know that it's going to be a catastrophe.

422
00:22:15,890 --> 00:22:17,390
气象预报员可能会出错  总统先生
Weathermen can be wrong, Mr. President,

423
00:22:17,390 --> 00:22:19,200
但全国每个预报员不会都错
but not every weatherman in the country.

424
00:22:19,840 --> 00:22:21,380
好吧  即使成真
All right, even if that's true,

425
00:22:21,440 --> 00:22:22,180
你也应该攻击她
you should attack her

426
00:22:22,180 --> 00:22:25,140
借飓风给自己拉同情票
for using the hurricane to score sympathy points.

427
00:22:26,890 --> 00:22:28,490
我已经和我手下讨论过了
I've discussed it with my staff.

428
00:22:28,970 --> 00:22:30,870
这不只是你的竞选  杰姬
This isn't just your campaign, Jackie,

429
00:22:30,870 --> 00:22:32,440
这是我们两个的竞选
this is our campaign.

430
00:22:35,520 --> 00:22:37,340
我能给您点建议吗  先生
May I offer you some advice, sir?

431
00:22:37,690 --> 00:22:38,630
签署那份法案吧
Sign the bill.

432
00:22:38,750 --> 00:22:40,720
如果您不签  飓风真的来了
If you don't, and the storm hits,

433
00:22:40,720 --> 00:22:42,540
我们就根本没得可竞选了
you and I won't have a campaign.

434
00:22:43,950 --> 00:22:45,510
你还是好好吃你的晚饭吧
You should get back to your dinner.

435
00:23:20,520 --> 00:23:23,130
大家先暂停一下
Hey, everyone. Let's put down the dishes for a second.

436
00:23:23,130 --> 00:23:24,100
