情况是这样
Here's the deal.

438
00:23:27,040 --> 00:23:29,260
我因为《美国就业法案》才雇了你们三个
I hired you three under America Works.

439
00:23:29,550 --> 00:23:31,490
虽然我们确实需要人手
And as much as we can use the manpower,

440
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:33,810
但如果法案中止  我负担不起这么多人
I can't afford it if the program gets ended.

441
00:23:34,540 --> 00:23:38,250
如果你们轮班的话  我或许能负担得起两个
I might be able to afford to keep two of you if you split shifts,

442
00:23:38,320 --> 00:23:39,710
但你们三个肯定不能都留下
but I can't keep all three.

443
00:23:43,450 --> 00:23:45,620
"这场飓风已经酝酿了不只数周
"A storm has been forming not for weeks,

444
00:23:45,620 --> 00:23:46,870
而是数十年
but for decades.

445
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:49,550
飓风的名字不是费斯  而是弗兰西斯
Its name is not Faith, it's Francis.

446
00:23:49,550 --> 00:23:51,890
全国上下均在他的路径上
The entire nation is in his path,

447
00:23:51,890 --> 00:23:53,610
而如果我们无视警钟
and if we ignore the warning signs,

448
00:23:53,610 --> 00:23:56,030
就只能怪自己了"
we have no one but ourselves to blame."

449
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:00,590
这不是一篇报道  是一篇评论
It's not an article. It's an opinion piece.

450
00:24:00,590 --> 00:24:01,350
我知道
I know.

451
00:24:02,410 --> 00:24:04,560
报纸不能采取这个社论立场
The paper can't take this editorial stance.

452
00:24:04,570 --> 00:24:05,960
-太多臆测了  -我知道
- It's too speculative. - I'm aware.

453
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:06,980
可以作为专栏发表
Print it as a column.

454
00:24:06,980 --> 00:24:09,600
一旦我那样做  你就越界了
The moment I do that, you cross over to the other side.

455
00:24:09,600 --> 00:24:11,340
我们就不能再让你做现在的工作了
We can't keep you on your beat.

456
00:24:11,500 --> 00:24:12,670
那就换掉我
So replace me.

457
00:24:13,370 --> 00:24:15,220
我想做专栏  是时候了
I want a column. It's time.

458
00:24:15,220 --> 00:24:17,080
凯特  你现在可以一路升到总编辑
Kate, you're on track to be managing editor.

459
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:18,080
如果你变成一名专栏作家
You toss that out the window

460
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:20,030
大好前途就毁了
the moment you switch over to being a columnist.

461
00:24:20,030 --> 00:24:21,980
我不想去编辑其他人的文字
I don't want to be editing other people's words.

462
00:24:22,690 --> 00:24:24,150
我想写我自己的文字
I want to be writing my own.

463
00:24:24,290 --> 00:24:26,480
而且不只是新闻  我希望能说出我的想法
And not just the news, I want my ideas out there.

464
00:24:26,480 --> 00:24:29,280
你知道你想干什么《电讯报》都会同意
Look. You know the Telegraph will let you do anything you want.

465
00:24:29,300 --> 00:24:31,710
但我们需要你报道总统
But we need you reporting on the President.

466
00:24:31,710 --> 00:24:33,850
-没人比你干得好  -我的偏见很明显
- Nobody does it better. - My bias is clear.

467
00:24:33,850 --> 00:24:36,060
你本来也不该再让我做报道了
You shouldn't keep me on as a reporter anyway.

468
00:24:37,100 --> 00:24:40,520
这样吧  我们可以把这变成一篇分析文章
I'll tell you what. We can make this work as an analysis piece.

469
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:44,120
你砍掉一些推测成分  着重事实和引述
You tone down the speculation, stick to the facts and quotes--

470
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:46,080
-整篇文章重点就在于推测  -好吧
- Speculation is the entire point. - Fine.

471
00:24:46,080 --> 00:24:46,750
至少...
Just...

472
00:24:47,290 --> 00:24:49,610
给我一点另一方的立场  平衡一下
give me a little something from the other side, to balance it out.

473
00:24:49,610 --> 00:24:51,180
你明知道他们不会对我说什么
You know they're not gonna give me a quote.

474
00:24:51,180 --> 00:24:52,270
哪怕只是一个
Even if it's a source just

475
00:24:52,270 --> 00:24:54,850
和政府有点擦边关联的信息源
tangentially associated with the administration.

476
00:24:54,850 --> 00:24:55,440
你这样做了
You do that,

477
00:24:55,440 --> 00:24:58,110
我们就能既发表文章又让你继续做记者
we can print this and keep you as a reporter.

478
00:25:01,430 --> 00:25:03,220
我想到我能和谁谈了
I got an idea who I can talk to.

479
00:25:05,930 --> 00:25:08,740
"也许换一天  水不那么冷
"On another day, with warmer water,

480
00:25:08,750 --> 00:25:10,260
水流也给他助力
with the current carrying him,

481
00:25:10,680 --> 00:25:11,780
他也许真能游到
he might have made it.

482
00:25:11,910 --> 00:25:12,730
但这天
But on this day,

483
00:25:12,730 --> 00:25:15,260
他游到一半时  胳膊再也挥不动了
he would only make it halfway before his arms gave out

484
00:25:15,260 --> 00:25:18,010
麻木彻底击溃了他  随后他被海岸警卫队
and the numbness overtook him, before the coast guard

485
00:25:18,010 --> 00:25:20,680
从水里救起  即便他非常不情愿
pulled him out of the water despite his protests.

486
00:25:20,940 --> 00:25:23,740
他鲁莽吗  他傻吗
Was he reckless? Was he foolish?

487
00:25:24,670 --> 00:25:25,660
可能吧
Possibly.

488
00:25:26,170 --> 00:25:28,050
不过有一件事是不容否认的
One thing can't be denied, however.

489
00:25:28,540 --> 00:25:32,700
其他人都认定不可能的  他却偏不相信
What others saw as impossible, he refused to believe as such.

490
00:25:33,190 --> 00:25:36,580
河水证明他错了  他离对岸还很远
The water proved him wrong. He fell far short of the other shore.

491
00:25:36,900 --> 00:25:38,930
但他还是尝试了
And yet he made the attempt.

492
00:25:39,380 --> 00:25:42,000
而这  就是一切"
And that... is everything."

493
00:25:48,020 --> 00:25:49,250
这只是序言
That's just the prologue.

494
00:25:53,360 --> 00:25:56,390
你一次都没提《美国就业法案》
You don't mention America Works once.

495
00:25:56,560 --> 00:25:57,460
我特意的
On purpose.

496
00:26:00,250 --> 00:26:03,120
这本书不就是写就业法案的吗
That is what the book is supposed to be about, isn't it?

497
00:26:03,590 --> 00:26:04,470
你不喜欢吗
You don't like it?

498
00:26:05,840 --> 00:26:08,390
我喜欢  我只是觉得
I do like it. I just wonder if I...

499
00:26:10,360 --> 00:26:14,820
也许我还不能理解你打算怎么写
Well, maybe I don't... understand what you're trying to do.

500
00:26:17,950 --> 00:26:19,320
没人单纯在乎一个理念
Nobody cares about an idea.

501
00:26:20,110 --> 00:26:22,040
人们也许会关注有理念的人
They might care about a man with an idea.

502
00:26:23,310 --> 00:26:25,700
而我只关注人
I only care about the man.

503
00:26:27,680 --> 00:26:30,910
整本书都会是这种风格  这种小品文
The whole book will be like this... these vignettes.

504
00:26:30,910 --> 00:26:33,680
就像短篇小说集似的
Like a collection of short stories.

505
00:26:34,460 --> 00:26:36,730
你提到《美就法》了吗
Do you mention AmWorks anywhere?

506
00:26:37,840 --> 00:26:38,630
没有
Nope.

507
00:26:40,530 --> 00:26:41,420
一次都没提过
Not once.

508
00:26:48,210 --> 00:26:50,150
我确实希望这书与众不同
I did want the book to be different,

509
00:26:50,150 --> 00:26:53,130
但我  只是觉得这样可能...
but I... It just seems that that might--

510
00:26:53,130 --> 00:26:55,850
我觉得这可能是我这些年写得最好的东西了
I think it might be the best thing I've written in years.

511
00:26:56,760 --> 00:26:59,620
当然也可能是彻头彻尾的垃圾
It could also be utter and complete shit.

512
00:27:00,730 --> 00:27:03,360
但我看不出是好是坏  这一般是好兆头
But when I can't tell the difference, it's usually a good sign.

513
00:27:05,500 --> 00:27:08,570
我只是希望不要偏离了大方向
I just don't want to lose sight of the bigger goal.

514
00:27:08,770 --> 00:27:10,350
我只会这么写
I don't know any other way to write it.

515
00:27:12,720 --> 00:27:13,850
如果这样不合你的意
If you want something different,

516
00:27:14,330 --> 00:27:16,640
最好现在就换人
now's the time to find somebody else.

517
00:27:16,640 --> 00:27:18,170
不  我希望你写完
No, I want you to finish it.

518
00:27:20,180 --> 00:27:21,190
虽然我不知道
Even though I have...

519
00:27:23,020 --> 00:27:25,960
如果我签了法案  你这书怎么写
no idea if it will end up being relevant if I end up...

520
00:27:27,600 --> 00:27:29,150
还有什么要紧
signing this bill.

521
00:27:29,580 --> 00:27:30,470
你打算签吗
Are you going to?

522
00:27:32,970 --> 00:27:34,370
我还不知道
I don't know yet.

523
00:27:35,240 --> 00:27:36,290
当然  就算我签了法案
If I do, of course,

524
00:27:36,290 --> 00:27:40,310
你的书用不着了  我还是会付全额稿酬的
I'll pay you in full if the book becomes unnecessary.

525
00:27:41,610 --> 00:27:43,180
我写这书不是为了钱
I'm not doing this for the paycheck.

526
00:27:47,610 --> 00:27:48,580
你有什么看法
What do you think?

527
00:27:50,150 --> 00:27:51,170
我该不该签
Should I sign it?

528
00:27:51,290 --> 00:27:52,560
这牵涉到我的利益
Well, I have skin in the game.

529
00:27:53,440 --> 00:27:55,280
所以出于私心  我希望你别签
So the selfish part of me says no.

530
00:27:58,240 --> 00:27:59,000
不过
But...

531
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:01,910
老实说
honestly?

532
00:28:03,190 --> 00:28:05,240
没有哪本书值得让人送命
No book is worth people losing their lives.

533
00:28:05,240 --> 00:28:07,180
话是没错  但这不只关系到这本书
Yes, but it's not just about the book.

534
00:28:08,630 --> 00:28:10,570
也是为了让人们重回工作岗位
It's about putting people back to work.

535
00:28:10,960 --> 00:28:12,610
如果人都死了  还怎么工作呢
People can't work if they're dead.

536
00:28:16,610 --> 00:28:19,980
我最近一段时间内
Well, I'm gonna obviously be very occupied

537
00:28:19,980 --> 00:28:22,350
都会为这个飓风忙里忙外
by this hurricane for the foreseeable future.

538
00:28:22,940 --> 00:28:24,320
再让我考虑考虑吧
Let me think on this for...

539
00:28:28,640 --> 00:28:30,090
你最好别坑他
You'd better not fuck him over.

540
00:28:30,910 --> 00:28:32,810
-什么  -你写的东西
- Excuse me? - With what you're writing.

541
00:28:33,860 --> 00:28:34,820
我也没这个打算
I don't intend to.

542
00:28:35,230 --> 00:28:37,560
-你在书里说他傻  -你偷听
- The part about being foolish? - You eavesdropping?

543
00:28:37,600 --> 00:28:39,810
-他不傻  -我也没说他傻
- He's not foolish. - That wasn't my point.

544
00:28:39,810 --> 00:28:41,740
我不会为个傻子挡子弹
I wouldn't take a bullet for a man who was.

545
00:28:44,790 --> 00:28:46,000
走吧  你的车已经候着了
Let's go, your car's waiting.

546
00:28:49,340 --> 00:28:50,300
从明天起
As of tomorrow,

547
00:28:50,300 --> 00:28:53,740
夏普议员女士和我将暂停竞选活动
Congresswoman Sharp and I are suspending our campaigns.

548
00:28:54,180 --> 00:28:57,010
我们将赶赴受飓风费斯影响的地区
We will be traveling to areas affected by Hurricane Faith,

549
00:28:57,010 --> 00:28:58,620
整个竞选团队也将随行
along with our campaign staff,

550
00:28:59,060 --> 00:29:02,590
以便为灾区贡献我们最大的力量
in order to volunteer in whatever capacity is most helpful.

551
00:29:03,330 --> 00:29:05,440
我们也将暂停接受捐款
We're also suspending any donations,

552
00:29:05,440 --> 00:29:08,370
同时呼吁我们的支持者向红十字会
and urge our supporters to donate to the Red Cross

553
00:29:08,580 --> 00:29:10,510
和其他飓风援助机构捐款
and other hurricane relief agencies.

554
00:29:10,740 --> 00:29:14,740
大灾当前  理应暂停政治活动
In times of suffering, it's important to suspend politics

555
00:29:15,000 --> 00:29:16,930
做对国家有益之事
and do what's best for the country.

556
00:29:17,940 --> 00:29:19,850
我们期待在飓风过去
We look forward to resuming our campaigns

557
00:29:19,850 --> 00:29:21,170
东海岸人民安全之后
when the storm has cleared

558
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:23,290
重启竞选活动
and the people of the east coast are safe.

559
00:29:24,200 --> 00:29:26,100
以上是民主党总统竞选候选人...
That was democratic precedencial candidate...

560
00:29:26,930 --> 00:29:27,750
弗莱迪
Freddy?

561
00:29:31,540 --> 00:29:33,480
总统想见你  海耶斯先生
The President would like to see you, Mr. Hayes.

562
00:29:34,780 --> 00:29:37,100
我还有两小时才能下班
I still got two hours left on my shift.

563
00:29:37,100 --> 00:29:38,830
没关系  弗莱迪  你可以走了
It's fine, Freddy. You can go.

564
00:29:40,250 --> 00:29:42,310
我能带上我孙子吗
Do you mind if I bring my grandson?

565
00:29:43,150 --> 00:29:45,350
因为飓风  日托所关了
Daycare got shut down 'cause of the storm.

566
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:48,160
当然可以  有车等着我们
Of course. We got a car waiting.

567
00:29:49,860 --> 00:29:50,980
走吧  杜肖恩
Come on, DeShawn.

568
00:29:54,470 --> 00:29:56,420
我们去见总统
We going to see the president.

569
00:30:01,040 --> 00:30:01,960
弗莱迪
Freddy.

570
00:30:05,830 --> 00:30:08,100
-很高兴见到你  弗兰克  -谢谢你能来
- It's good to see you, Frank. - Thank you for coming.

571
00:30:08,390 --> 00:30:11,830
这就是杜肖恩吧  你好吗  先生
And this must be DeShawn. How are you, sir?

572
00:30:12,190 --> 00:30:14,320
握手真是坚定有力
That is a firm handshake you have.

573
00:30:15,380 --> 00:30:17,480
你想去那张桌子后面坐坐吗
Well, you want to go over and sit at the desk?

574
00:30:18,640 --> 00:30:19,470
去吧
Go ahead.

575
00:30:29,440 --> 00:30:31,180
有时候我也那么干
Yeah, I do that too, sometimes.

576
00:30:33,110 --> 00:30:35,670
那桌子有一天或许会是你的
That desk might be yours one day.

577
00:30:36,560 --> 00:30:38,290
你想当总统吗
Would you like to be the president?

578
00:30:39,900 --> 00:30:40,580
想
Yeah.

579
00:30:40,690 --> 00:30:44,390
要当总统  你得在学校取得好成绩
Well, to be president, you have to get good grades in school.

580
00:30:44,390 --> 00:30:46,670
我看你带了作业来
Now, I see you brought some of your schoolwork with you.

581
00:30:46,670 --> 00:30:49,050
我那边有个办公室
I have an office just around the corner in here,

582
00:30:49,050 --> 00:30:50,990
你或许愿意去那里做作业
maybe you'd like to go do your work in there.

583
00:30:50,990 --> 00:30:54,630
如果你想玩  我们还有游戏机
Or we also have a PlayStation if you'd rather play that.

584
00:30:55,690 --> 00:30:57,800
-你有什么游戏  -很多呢
- What games you got? - Oh, we have plenty of games.

585
00:30:57,800 --> 00:30:58,970
密查姆会带你去
Meechum will show you.

586
00:31:08,570 --> 00:31:09,690
给你拿点什么喝
What can I get for you?

587
00:31:09,720 --> 00:31:11,400
咖啡  苏打水  还是啤酒
Coffee, a soda, a beer?

588
00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:13,530
-不用了  谢谢  -请坐
- No, I'm good, thank you. - Please sit down.

589
00:31:18,550 --> 00:31:21,370
-你注册了《美就法》  -是的
- You signed up for America Works. - I did.

590
00:31:21,520 --> 00:31:24,620
我有四万个你这样的案例
I've got 40,000 case studies just like yours.

591
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:27,260
我桌上还有一份法案
And I also have a bill on my desk

592
00:31:27,260 --> 00:31:29,830
会斩断支持这四万人的资金
that's gonna cut the funding for all 40,000.

593
00:31:29,830 --> 00:31:31,760
知道  我看新闻了
Yeah, I been following on the news.

594
00:31:32,390 --> 00:31:33,470
我会签了它
I'm gonna sign it.

595
00:31:33,710 --> 00:31:36,100
这场飓风危及太多生命了
There's too many lives at stake with this storm.

596
00:31:36,400 --> 00:31:38,030
听起来那是正确的做法
Sounds like the right thing to do.

597
00:31:38,730 --> 00:31:40,210
弗莱迪  你该有份工作
Freddy, you deserve a job,

598
00:31:40,210 --> 00:31:42,460
而国会在强迫我剥夺它
and Congress is forcing me to take it away.

599
00:31:42,860 --> 00:31:44,560
我跟我们的运营主管谈过
I've spoken to our head of operations,

600
00:31:44,560 --> 00:31:46,970
如果你愿意  这里有份给你的工作
and if you want it, there's a job for you here.

601
00:31:46,970 --> 00:31:49,260
-这不是施舍你  但...  -薪水多少
- Now, it's not charity, but-- - What's the pay?

602
00:31:50,200 --> 00:31:51,800
我不知道具体数字
Well, I don't know the exact figures,

603
00:31:51,810 --> 00:31:54,420
但我猜大概每月三千美金左右吧
but I figure somewhere around three grand a month.

604
00:31:54,420 --> 00:31:56,270
-我知道不多  但...  -医保有吗
- I know that's not great, but I-- - Healthcare?

605
00:31:57,710 --> 00:31:58,920
当然有  包括那个
Well, yes, of course. That's included.

606
00:31:58,920 --> 00:32:01,610
-杜肖恩能用吗  -当然  所有家属都能用
- For DeShawn, too? - That's right. All dependents.

607
00:32:02,210 --> 00:32:04,310
-什么工作  -厨房
- What's the job? - The kitchen.

608
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:06,930
帮厨师们备菜
Helping prep food for the chefs.

609
00:32:07,350 --> 00:32:10,630
只要薪水在每月两千八以上
Well, as long as it's, you know, above 2,800 a month.

610
00:32:10,630 --> 00:32:11,900
我需要那么多来付房租
That's what I need to make my rent

611
00:32:11,900 --> 00:32:14,080
并保证杜肖恩什么都不缺
and make sure DeShawn has everything he needs.

612
00:32:14,080 --> 00:32:16,360
我马上帮你联系主厨
I'll put you in touch with the head chef right away.

613
00:32:16,830 --> 00:32:19,860
不知道...你还有其他工作吗
I was wondering... if you had anything else?

614
00:32:20,430 --> 00:32:23,170
-除了厨房的  -我以为...
- Besides the kitchen. - Well, I just assumed that--

615
00:32:23,170 --> 00:32:25,290
我一辈子都在厨房里工作
I've been working in kitchens my whole life.

616
00:32:25,560 --> 00:32:28,920
我虽开过肋排馆不代表我喜欢厨房
Just 'cause I owned a rib joint don't mean I like working in 'em.

617
00:32:28,970 --> 00:32:30,350
那你想做什么
Well, what would you rather do?

618
00:32:31,940 --> 00:32:33,850
我看你们雇了园丁
You got groundskeepers out there.

619
00:32:34,440 --> 00:32:37,280
车开进来时我看到他们在给树剪枝
I noticed 'em choppin' branches when we were driving in,

620
00:32:37,280 --> 00:32:38,220
为飓风做准备
for the hurricane.

621
00:32:39,190 --> 00:32:40,330
你喜欢那个
You'd prefer that?

622
00:32:40,840 --> 00:32:42,520
一直都想在室外工作
Always wanted to work outside.

623
00:32:43,230 --> 00:32:45,670
这肯定可以安排
Well, I'm sure that something can be arranged.

624
00:32:48,770 --> 00:32:50,080
我也想哪天能当总统
I want to be president one day.

625
00:32:50,320 --> 00:32:53,040
-那永远不可能  -但他说我可以
- Well, that's never gonna happen. - But he said I could be.

626
00:32:53,690 --> 00:32:56,440
听着  孩子  他骗你的
Listen up, boy. He lied to you.

627
00:32:56,560 --> 00:32:58,820
事实是  你永远不可能当上总统
The truth is, you ain't never gonna be president.

628
00:32:59,260 --> 00:33:03,170
就像你海报里的那些篮球运动员
It's just like them basketball players you got posters of.

629
00:33:03,170 --> 00:33:06,420
他们说你能做成任何事  当超级巨星
They say you can do anything, be a superstar, too.

630
00:33:06,650 --> 00:33:09,750
但他们基因好  能长两米多  如果不是呢
But they were born to be seven feet tall and if they wasn't,

631
00:33:09,750 --> 00:33:11,110
你说说他们还能有什么
tell me what would they have?

632
00:33:11,630 --> 00:33:12,570
一无所有
Nothing.

633
00:33:12,810 --> 00:33:15,280
他们中有一半连字都不识
Half of them can't even read a damn book.

634
00:33:15,650 --> 00:33:18,200
孩子  这里不是你我能待的地方
No, boy, this place ain't for you and me.

635
00:33:18,440 --> 00:33:22,940
有梦想是好事  别妄想就行
It's good to have dreams, just so long as they're not fantasies.

636
00:33:22,940 --> 00:33:25,930
如果你被这套糊弄了  就只能怪自己了
You let anybody sell you that shit, it's your own damn fault.

637
00:33:25,930 --> 00:33:27,830
-听见了吗  -听见了  爷爷
- You hear me? - Yeah, I hear you, Pop.

638
00:33:46,220 --> 00:33:47,560
我立即送去国会
I'll get it to the House right away.

639
00:33:48,490 --> 00:33:50,280
-能通知媒体吗  -可以
- Green light on the release? - Yes.

640
00:33:58,550 --> 00:34:00,290
我不记得给过你我的号码
I don't remember giving you my phone number.

641
00:34:00,290 --> 00:34:02,270
你是没给  你的出版商给了
You didn't. Your publisher did.

642
00:34:02,770 --> 00:34:04,020
他想让我写本书
He wants me to write a book.

643
00:34:04,930 --> 00:34:06,280
你没出过书我倒觉得意外
I'm surprised you never have.

644
00:34:07,050 --> 00:34:09,930
我敢说不管你写什么都会卖得有我十倍好
I'm sure any book you wrote would do ten times what mine do.

645
00:34:10,880 --> 00:34:12,430
肯定赶不上《天蝎》
Not as much as Scorpio.

646
00:34:15,020 --> 00:34:16,420
比我之后的作品好
As any I've written since.

647
00:34:17,230 --> 00:34:18,380
我上大学时看的
I read it in college.

648
00:34:19,080 --> 00:34:20,290
改变你人生了吗
Did it change your life?

649
00:34:21,630 --> 00:34:23,330
你是不是整天听人说这个
That's what you hear all day long, isn't it?

650
00:34:23,330 --> 00:34:26,510
那得有人能在大街上认出我  不过没有
If I still got recognized on the street, which I don't.

651
00:34:26,510 --> 00:34:27,710
主要是在签售会上
Mostly at book signings,

652
00:34:27,720 --> 00:34:30,410
如果你写书  我建议你别开签售会
which I don't recommend if you write your book.

653
00:34:30,490 --> 00:34:32,360
我请你来不是讨论我的书的
I didn't ask you here to discuss my book.

654
00:34:32,730 --> 00:34:34,410
-不是吗  -我想谈谈你的书
- No? - I want to discuss yours.

655
00:34:36,590 --> 00:34:38,880
我正在写一篇报道  如果没有白宫的评论
I'm working on a piece, and it won't go to print

656
00:34:38,880 --> 00:34:41,010
我就没法刊登出去
unless I get a comment from the White House.

657
00:34:41,790 --> 00:34:42,720
我不为白宫干活
I'm not a part of the White House.

658
00:34:42,720 --> 00:34:43,680
不非得是原话
Doesn't even have to be a quote,

659
00:34:43,680 --> 00:34:47,130
只要让我能改述一下就行  比如说
just something... that I can paraphrase, like,

660
00:34:47,410 --> 00:34:50,030
"据与政府联系紧密  不愿透露姓名人士称"
"According to someone close to the administration..."

661
00:34:50,280 --> 00:34:51,700
不非得公开
Doesn't have to be on the record.

662
00:34:51,710 --> 00:34:53,260
我不会就我的书发表评论的
I'm not commenting on the book.

663
00:34:53,510 --> 00:34:55,470
汤姆  你能知道别人无从得知的事
Tom, you got access no one else has.

664
00:34:55,470 --> 00:34:57,440
有原因的  因为他知道我管得住嘴
For a reason. 'Cause he knows I won't talk.

665
00:34:57,710 --> 00:34:59,030
尤其是对你
Especially to you.

666
00:35:02,310 --> 00:35:03,510
我总可以请你喝一杯吧
Well, can I buy you a drink?

667
00:35:04,310 --> 00:35:05,650
灌醉我可不好使
Getting me drunk won't work.

668
00:35:05,760 --> 00:35:07,790
你大老远来见我  我欠你一杯酒
You came out to meet me here. I owe you one.

669
00:35:10,200 --> 00:35:11,530
不如我请你喝一杯
Why don't I buy you a drink?

670
00:35:13,480 --> 00:35:14,680
多来几杯怎么样
How about we have a few?

671
00:35:16,750 --> 00:35:17,830
多几杯啊
A few.

672
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:20,070
行啊
I can live with that.

673
00:35:26,780 --> 00:35:29,660
我真遗憾  弗兰西斯  我知道这有多难
I'm so sorry, Francis. I know how hard this is.

674
00:35:29,700 --> 00:35:32,420
我也没办法啊  天气我管不了
It was out of my hands. I can't control the weather.

675
00:35:33,350 --> 00:35:34,260
终究不好受
Still.

676
00:35:36,620 --> 00:35:38,400
最让我不痛快的
What frustrates me more than anything

677
00:35:38,400 --> 00:35:39,880
就是我们本来已经开始扭转局面了
is we were starting to turn the ship.

678
00:35:39,880 --> 00:35:42,440
国会开始支持我了  再过几个月
I was getting support in Congress. A few more months...

679
00:35:42,600 --> 00:35:44,490
领导层就将别无选择
and the leadership would've had no choice

680
00:35:44,490 --> 00:35:46,380
只能支持《美国就业法案》
but to support America Works.

681
00:35:49,790 --> 00:35:51,790
如果能让你好受些  凯茜刚刚打来电话
Well, if it's any solace, Cathy just called.

682
00:35:51,790 --> 00:35:54,330
俄罗斯方面愿意出兵
The Russians are willing to contribute troops.

683
00:35:55,020 --> 00:35:56,510
参加维和部队吗
To the peacekeeping force?

684
00:35:56,510 --> 00:35:57,850
他们不想被落下
They don't want to be left out.

685
00:35:58,920 --> 00:36:00,550
没开什么条件吗
No catch, no conditions?

686
00:36:00,550 --> 00:36:03,550
没有  他们在联合国背负了巨大压力
None. There's too much pressure on them in the UN.

687
00:36:03,570 --> 00:36:05,060
孤立策略起作用了
So the isolation worked.

688
00:36:05,470 --> 00:36:07,170
他们派遣三百名士兵
They're sending 300 troops.

689
00:36:08,230 --> 00:36:09,540
太好了
That's incredible.

690
00:36:09,940 --> 00:36:12,900
-我们成功了  -不是我们  是你自己
- We did it. - Oh, no, not we. It was all you.

691
00:36:14,390 --> 00:36:16,440
-一起吃晚饭吧  -我要睡觉了
- Join me for dinner? - I'm gonna turn in.

692
00:36:16,730 --> 00:36:17,670
睡这么早
This early, huh?

693
00:36:17,690 --> 00:36:20,320
等飓风刮过来  我三天都别想睡了
I'm gonna be up three straight days once this hurricane hits.

694
00:36:20,320 --> 00:36:22,070
我得抓紧多睡会儿
I need to get all the sleep I can.

695
00:36:23,260 --> 00:36:25,310
好主意  那你睡吧
That's a good idea. I'll leave you be.

696
00:36:30,480 --> 00:36:33,070
等飓风登陆了  让管家通知我
Have one of the stewards wake me when it hits the coast.

697
00:36:53,120 --> 00:36:54,030
弗兰西斯
Francis.

698
00:36:55,960 --> 00:36:56,880
弗兰西斯
Francis?

699
00:37:02,180 --> 00:37:03,580
登陆点在哪
Where did it make landfall?

700
00:37:04,080 --> 00:37:06,560
-没登陆  -什么
- It didn't. - What?

701
00:37:06,690 --> 00:37:08,080
飓风调头了
The hurricane turned.

702
00:37:11,770 --> 00:37:14,600
现在朝东行进了  可能会到百慕大
It's due east now. It might hit Bermuda.

703
00:37:15,010 --> 00:37:15,900
不过
But it'll, uh,

704
00:37:16,240 --> 00:37:18,770
因为已经到了较冷海面  飓风会很快消散
dissipate quickly now that it's reaching colder water.

705
00:37:19,340 --> 00:37:21,380
看来我们逃过一劫  总统先生
It looks like we dodged a bullet, Mr. President.

706
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:24,870
我的资金都来不及进行半吊子的应急准备
I barely got the money in time for a halfway decent response.

707
00:37:34,120 --> 00:37:35,600
怎样才能撤回法案
How do we pull back on the bill?

708
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:37,560
已经送到国会并通知媒体了
Already delivered to Congress, we put out a release.

709
00:37:37,560 --> 00:37:39,080
肯定有什么议事规则
There must be some parliamentary procedure

710
00:37:39,080 --> 00:37:40,480
可以撤销我的签字
that will nullify my signature.

711
00:37:40,500 --> 00:37:42,120
我已经咨询过白宫律师团
I checked with the White House counsel.

712
00:37:42,120 --> 00:37:43,160
法案已经正式成为法律了
The bill is officially law

713
00:37:43,170 --> 00:37:44,730
资金也已经拨出去了
and the money's already been appropriated.

714
00:37:51,470 --> 00:37:55,340
联邦应急管理署正帮助数千疏散民众返回家中
FEMA is assisting thousands of evacuees returning to their homes.

715
00:37:55,340 --> 00:37:57,810
除佐治亚州受飓风外围影响
With the exception of moderate flooding in Georgia

716
00:37:57,810 --> 00:37:59,350
出现小规模洪水之外
due to rain from the outer bands,

717
00:37:59,600 --> 00:38:03,170
东海岸其他地区基本上毫发无伤
the rest of the Eastern Seaboard was left virtually untouched

718
00:38:03,170 --> 00:38:06,480
而大家原本预期这将是百年一遇的风灾
by the hurricane everyone expected to be the storm of the century.

719
00:38:06,480 --> 00:38:09,870
飓风费斯造成的最大损失不是人员财产损失
The biggest casualty to Faith was not life or property, however,

720
00:38:09,930 --> 00:38:11,450
而是安德伍德总统
but rather President Underwood's

721
00:38:11,450 --> 00:38:13,860
饱受争议的美国就业计划
controversial America Works plan,

722
00:38:13,880 --> 00:38:16,740
国会为应对飓风救灾
which Congress defunded in order to free up resources

723
00:38:16,740 --> 00:38:18,830
已撤回了其资金
for storm-related disaster relief.

724
00:38:18,910 --> 00:38:22,250
总统因受来自国会两党和媒体的巨大压力
The president himself signed the emergency appropriation into law

725
00:38:22,260 --> 00:38:26,230
签署了这项紧急拨款法案
after facing immense pressure from both parties and the media.

726
00:38:29,190 --> 00:38:30,990
看来你失业了
So you're out of a job, I guess.

727
00:38:32,300 --> 00:38:35,280
可能吧  又不是第一次了 
Probably. Wouldn't be the first time.

728
00:38:36,960 --> 00:38:38,090
不知道能不能让你好受些
If it makes you feel any better,

729
00:38:38,100 --> 00:38:40,120
但是我的报道也彻底没戏了
there's no way my story'll get printed now.

730
00:38:41,100 --> 00:38:43,850
为什么  因为我不愿意给你评论吗
Why? Because I wouldn't give you a quote?

731
00:38:43,880 --> 00:38:46,500
不  整篇都是飓风比喻
No, it was a whole hurricane metaphor.

732
00:38:47,430 --> 00:38:49,850
没有飓风的话  也没什么力度了
Kind of takes the wind out of the sails if there's no hurricane.

733
00:38:54,220 --> 00:38:55,670
至少你性福了一把
at least you got laid.

734
00:38:57,000 --> 00:38:59,970
没错  这么说还真诗意
Yep. That... that's poetic.

735
00:39:00,600 --> 00:39:03,300
我是作家嘛
Yeah. I'm a writer.

736
00:39:15,060 --> 00:39:17,100
-怎么了  -我得走了
- What is it? - I gotta go.

737
00:39:18,270 --> 00:39:19,500
你这是想赶我走吗
Is that your way of getting rid of me?

738
00:39:20,250 --> 00:39:22,330
不  是总统
No. It's the president.

739
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:31,520
我需要你把衬衫还给我
I'm gonna need the shirt back.

740
00:39:42,910 --> 00:39:45,200
如果你叫我来是解雇我  那完全没必要
If you asked me over to let me go, it wasn't necessary.

741
00:39:45,200 --> 00:39:47,770
-但我感激你的周到  -我没说要解雇你
- But I appreciate the thoughtfulness. - I'm not letting you go.

742
00:39:47,770 --> 00:39:49,590
这本书现在更重要了
This book is more important now than ever.

743
00:39:49,670 --> 00:39:52,050
但是  《美国就业法案》已经完了
But... America Works is done.

744
00:39:52,050 --> 00:39:54,210
那就只剩一种办法使之重回正轨了
Well, there's only one way to get it back on track.

745
00:39:54,820 --> 00:39:57,530
我要宣布参加2016年总统大选了
I'm announcing my candidacy for 2016.

746
00:39:58,170 --> 00:39:59,310
我之前不能选
I couldn't run before.

747
00:39:59,310 --> 00:40:00,070
我既没有竞选经费
I didn't have the money

748
00:40:00,070 --> 00:40:01,670
也没有领导层的支持
and I didn't have the leadership's backing.

749
00:40:01,760 --> 00:40:04,450
但我已经证明了《美就法》的前景
But now that I've proven what AmWorks can do,

750
00:40:04,640 --> 00:40:06,800
我会得到经费和党内支持的
the money and the support will be there.

751
00:40:07,010 --> 00:40:10,410
支持弗兰克·安德伍德就是支持《美国就业法案》
A vote for Frank Underwood is a vote for America Works.

752
00:40:10,880 --> 00:40:12,860
-你说得对  -我说对什么了
- You were right. - How was I right?

753
00:40:13,810 --> 00:40:15,650
过来看看窗外
Come over here, take a look out the window.

754
00:40:20,850 --> 00:40:22,710
看见在那边忙活的那个人了吗
You see that man working over there?

755
00:40:23,260 --> 00:40:26,080
-那是弗莱迪·海耶斯  -肋排哥
- That's Freddy Hayes. - The ribs guy?

756
00:40:26,200 --> 00:40:30,020
-他现在是园丁了  -你真好心
- He's a groundskeeper now. - That's generous of you.

757
00:40:30,020 --> 00:40:32,260
不  不是好心  是我的职责
No, it wasn't. It's my job.

758
00:40:32,760 --> 00:40:36,160
你书里写我拒绝相信不可能
You wrote that I refuse to see the impossible as impossible.

759
00:40:36,270 --> 00:40:37,750
弗莱迪只是一份工作
Freddy is one job.

760
00:40:37,790 --> 00:40:39,910
我还有千万个要安排
I have ten million more to go.

761
00:40:40,250 --> 00:40:42,810
那才是我的故事  那才是你说对的事
That's my story and that's why you were right.

762
00:40:43,570 --> 00:40:45,100
你想继续写下去吗
So you wanna get back to work?

763
00:40:46,130 --> 00:40:46,960
我想
I'm in.

764
00:40:48,230 --> 00:40:50,880
现在就写吗  我没带笔记本
Now? I don't have my notebook.

765
00:40:58,030 --> 00:41:00,440
这是我签署法案用的笔
The pen I signed the bill with.

766
00:41:03,500 --> 00:41:05,410
好  开始吧
All right. Let's do it.

767
00:41:05,690 --> 00:41:07,970
我从未企图游泳渡河去萨姆特堡
I never tried to swim to Fort Sumter.

768
00:41:08,180 --> 00:41:11,210
托马斯可能知道是我编的  但他还是写了
Thomas probably knows I made it up, but he wrote about it anyway

769
00:41:11,210 --> 00:41:13,470
因为他理解更重要的真理
because he understands the greater truth:

770
00:41:13,790 --> 00:41:17,210
想象力也是一种勇气
imagination is its own form of courage.

771
00:41:18,800 --> 00:41:20,370
我们再谈谈那次渡河的事
Let's talk more about that swim.

772
00:41:20,620 --> 00:41:23,110
我的确只差这么一点就淹死了
I really did come this close to drowning.

773
00:41:25,210 --> 00:41:35,210
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}2005年  飓风卡特里娜扫过佛罗里达州后  经墨西哥湾在新奥尔良登陆
由于风力极强  登陆时给当地建筑交通用电等造成极大破坏
飓风登陆后  由于防水堤溃坝  导致水漫新奥尔良  进一步加重了灾情
时任总统的小布什乘专机赶到新奥尔良
当时白宫为了不影响救灾工作  小布什没有马上落地视察
但白宫发布小布什坐专机俯瞰灾区的照片后
却被媒体批为不体灾民疾苦  只在天上做做样子
此后小布什还在巡视联邦应急管理署时  对其署长的工作表示肯定
然而因为灾情严重  联邦应急管理署准备不足  救灾工作非常不得力
新奥尔良在飓风过之后很长时间都处于非常混乱的状态
所有这些灾后乱象都被媒体算在小布什的头上
认为是他指挥不力  不关心百姓疾苦
当时小布什已经因为中东战事进展不顺而倍受压力
卡特琳娜飓风在政治上给了他进一步的打击
此后他民望大跌  一直到他离开白宫  也没有恢复

774
00:41:50,210 --> 00:42:00,210
{\an5}{\pos(193,145)}2012年总统选举进入最后阶段
一直落后的共和党候选人罗姆尼凭借在电视辩论中的出色表现后来居上
开始在民调中领先奥巴马
就在共和党希望可以趁热打铁领先冲刺的时候
大西洋上突然升起的飓风桑迪扑向美国东海岸
登陆后  新泽西  纽约和新英格兰地区停水停电停油
大量房屋被毁坏  灾情十分严重
桑迪登陆后  奥巴马一分钟也没有浪费这个领导救灾的好机会
以总统身份到灾区一线视察指挥
同受到桑迪影响的各州州长携手出现在电视镜头前
大灾当前  刚刚占据选举上风的罗姆尼不得不暂停自己的竞选活动
把电视头条让给领导指挥救灾工作的奥巴马
在选举前的关键时刻被奥巴马抢了风头
风过之后  大选选情彻底改变  民调结果开始不相上下
最终罗姆尼在选举中败给了奥巴马

